The paper proposes a novel architecture for generative adversarial networks (GANs) that addresses the problem of limited and distributed datasets across multiple agents, while preserving data privacy. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The architecture is fully distributed and does not require a centralized controller, which could also place it under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also analyzes the interactions between the agents as a game, which could place it under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with multi-agent generative models, which could place it under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
